  "target_response": {
    "text": "You're in a normal position, not a worrying one. Step counts don't accumulate evenly — most people bank the bulk of their movement after midday, so a 1pm reading is a halftime score, not a result. You're at 4200 steps against a goal of 9000, which leaves 4800 to close across the rest of the day; a normal afternoon plus an ordinary evening routine covers most of that without special effort. Treat the goal as a progress target: the useful question at this hour is whether any movement is planned later, not whether the bar is filled yet. If today happens to have an open slot, a 30 to 40 min walk after dinner is worth roughly half the remaining gap on its own. Judge the day at bedtime — and judge the habit by the weekly pattern, not any single afternoon.",
